data.enText: to try to be more successful or better than sb else who is trying to do the same as you

data.chText: 为得到那项合同，几家公司正在竞争。
data.enText: Several companies are competing for the contract.

data.chText: 我们在价格上无法与他们竞争。
data.enText: We can't compete with them on price.

data.chText: 小孩子通常都会在母亲面前争宠。
data.enText: Young children will usually compete for their mother's attention.

data.chText: 面对廉价的外国进口商品，经营规模小的商人无法与之抗衡。
data.enText: Small traders cannot compete in the face of cheap foreign imports.
to take part in a contest or game

data.chText: 他期盼着参加伦敦马拉松比赛。
data.enText: He's hoping to compete in the London marathon.

simple_means.memory_skill: com 共同 + pet 寻求；力争 + e → 共同追求〔一个目标〕→ 竞争

value.def: When one firm or country competes with another, it tries to get people to buy its own goods in preference to those of the other firm or country. You can also say that two firms or countries compete .

example.ex: The banks have long competed with American Express's charge cards and various store cards...
example.tran: 长久以来，这些银行一直在与美国运通公司的信用卡以及各式各样的商场赊购卡竞争。

example.ex: The stores will inevitably end up competing with each other in their push for increased market shares...
example.tran: 在努力争取更大的市场份额的过程中，这些商场最终将不可避免地相互展开竞争。

example.ex: Banks and building societies are competing fiercely for business...
example.tran: 银行和购房互助协会为了争夺业务而展开激烈的竞争。

example.ex: The American economy, and its ability to compete abroad, was slowing down according to the report.
example.tran: 根据这项报告，美国经济及其海外竞争能力发展的速度开始放缓。

value.def: If you compete with someone for something, you try to get it for yourself and stop the other person getting it. You can also say that two people compete for something.

example.ex: Kangaroos compete with sheep and cattle for sparse supplies of food and water...
example.tran: 袋鼠与牛羊争夺稀少的食物和水。

example.ex: Schools should not compete with each other or attempt to poach pupils...
example.tran: 学校之间不应该相互竞争，也不应该企图挖走彼此的学生。

example.ex: More than 2300 candidates from 93 political parties are competing for 486 seats.
example.tran: 来自93个政党的2,300多位候选人将争夺486个席位。

value.def: If you compete in a contest or a game, you take part in it.

example.ex: He will be competing in the London-Calais-London race...
example.tran: 他将参加伦敦至加来的航海往返赛。

example.ex: Dubbed foreign language films will not be allowed to compete for best film...
example.tran: 外国译制片不得参加最佳影片的角逐。

example.ex: It is essential for all players who wish to compete that they earn computer ranking points.
example.tran: 对所有希望参赛的选手来说，获得电脑排名的分数非常重要。
